        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles north of Dillon, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dillon and Glen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
